//1. 

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>Document</title>
</head>
<body>
     <h1>HTML defines the content and structure of your website</h1>
</body>
</html>


//2.

comments in html are non-executable lines that we can write for explanation of code.
there are two types of comments: single line comment and multi line comment
comments are represented using <!-- line of code --!>


//3. 

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>Document</title>
</head>
<body>
     <h1>HTML defines the content and structure of your website</h1>
     <p>hello this is my paragraph this is second line of paragraph</p>
     <hr>
</body>
</html>


//4.

tags- basic building blocks used to write whole html document
2 types:
self closing-  there is no need to open and close these tags seperately. eg image tag
manual closing-  these tags are opened seprately and then closed seperately. eg paragraph tag and body tag


//5. 

doctype declaration: <!DOCTYPE html>
this tells that the html document we are working on is based on html5 
